FuncDef: The delete blacklist ipv6 command deletes specified IPv6 addresses or all IPv6 addresses from the HTTPS redirection blacklist.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the IPv6 address.
The value is a 32-digit hexadecimal number, in the format of X:X:X:X:X:X:X:X.

Indicates that all IPv6 addresses are to be deleted.
-

ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
If a user IPv6 address is added to the HTTPS redirection blacklist by accident, run the delete blacklist ipv6 command to delete specified IPv6 addresses or all IPv6 addresses from the HTTPS redirection blacklist.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
